                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d298">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum left at Department of State by Minister Wu.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chinese Legation</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-07-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 17, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cablegram received on July 17, 1900, from Viceroys Liu Kun Yi and Chang Chih-tung
                    and Director-General Sheng, dated July 16, 1900, retransmitted by the Chinese
                    minister in London, dated July 17, 1900, as follows:<quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Utmost efforts made to protect all foreign ministers who were well on
                            13th (July 9). If Tientsin city should be destroyed it would be
                            difficult to restore same in one hundred years. Request the powers to
                            preserve it, as the consequences would affect Chinese and foreign
                            commerce. Earl Li Hung Chang is transferred to north China (as viceroy
                            of Chihli). Please transmit this to Ministers Yang, Lu, Yu, and Wu.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
